		Comment <a href="#c_1713619513">7</a> by Tim Fitzpatrick
		posted on 8/2/2005 at 9:19 PM
		</div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p>Fantastic game and tech... for developers, probably the most interesting mod out there that is definitely worth a look is "Garry's mod", which basically harnesses the physics engine to allow you to build various strange constructions out of game elements, such as a giant robot made of oil drums and cars, held together with pulleys and ropes... a virtual erector set, if you will.</p><p>You really have to try it to fully see how cool it is.</p><p>BTW, I'm on my second run through the game... I finished it a few months back, but now downloaded the HL:Substance mod, that reworks the whole game by adding more monsters and new plus modified weapons everywhere... and also lets you shape-shift between the standard Gordon Freeman and 3 characters from the Metal Gear game series. The plot of the original game goes out the window somewhat with this mod, but it's a lot of fun.</p></div>
	</div>
</div>
		
